{
  "text": "To assess the level of population structure, we estimated various F statistics (table 3) by use of AMOVA [CITATION_1] ) and by taking into account interhaplotype molecular differences (see the \"Statistical Analysis\" subsection of the \"Subjects and Methods\" section). The overall F ST value calculated for the entire African sample, comprising 22 populations without groupings, was 0.342 (significantly greater than zero, ), indicating that Ϫ4 P ! 10 a large proportion of the overall Y-chromosome variation resulted from interpopulation differences. When the populations were partitioned into seven groups according to a geographic criterion, a high degree of both inter-and intragroup variability ( , ;",
